## Development Workflow


## Development Workflow
- Create entities and DTOs for each feature.
- Implement services and register with DI.
- Add endpoints or hubs as needed.
- Build UI components and pages.
- Style with Tailwind (mobile-first).
- Write tests for all public methods.


## Quick Checklist for New Features
- Entity and DTOs created for each feature
- Service created with async/await and CancellationToken
- Components are interactive with InteractiveWebAssembly if needed
- Styling uses Tailwind (mobile-first)
- DI configured in Program.cs
- API endpoints or hubs mapped (if applicable)
- Error handling with specific exceptions
- Unit tests written
- Null checks and input validation
- Logging for important operations

## Real-Time Features (Chat, Notifications)
- SignalR hub and client wrapper created
- Connection/disconnection and group management handled
- User authentication verified in hub
- Component subscribes/unsubscribes to events
- Proper disposal and reconnection logic
- Typing indicators and presence updates working

## Social App Security
- User privacy checks
- Block list verified before showing profiles
- Connection requests validated
- Chat messages only between connected users
- Age/gender filtering applied
- Rate limiting for sensitive actions
- Reported content flagged for moderation

